Deployment Models



Public cloud
- leverages publicly available cloud infrastructure over the internet
- resources are shared between orgs
- resources owned by service provider
- Advantages: not capital expenses, no maintenance, scalability, reliability


Private cloud
- Leverage privately-owned infra within an org's network
- Advantages: Flexibility (customize to your needs), Security, Scalable


Hybrid Cloud
- mix of public and private cloud
- Offers Cloud bursting which enables orgs to expand services from a private to public cloud in high demand situations
- Advantage: Cost effective, flexible, control (keep sensitive date in private, other stuff in public)
